<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98910395858287></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98910395858287><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98910395858287>RE: Skills</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=98910395858287#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=21128><span id= >Beetlebrow</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>53 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, May 5th 7:05 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.98]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Kadthar here,<br><br>I don't think you can really say any of the trade skills are best for a high elf magician.  Jewelry making is probably not worth the effort since you will need an enchanter to do anything worthwhile with it, other than make cute trinkets with no effect.  Tailoring provides a benefit early on, in allowing you to make a suit of raw silk for yourself.  Another possibility of a valuable trade skill for a high elf is blacksmithing which will allow you to make elven chain which you can wear.  This also requires an enchanter, though.  Brewing and baking are both fun, but of limited use to a magician, who can make his own food and is at a disadvantage when drunk, though you can make money through baking.  Whatever you decide, good luck.  :-)<br><br>Kadthar Al`Kreshid &lt;Midnight Unity&gt;<br>Level 25 Erudite Gatecaller (Magician)<br>Tholuxe Paells<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
