	   <tr><td colspan=2>To echo Zuranthium yet again, be a High elf, gnome, or Dark elf. All get infravision (DE's get ultravision) which means your day is 24 hours. If you want highest starting Int (of people who can see in the dark), be the DE. If you want life to be easy in Felwithe, Kelethin, Freeport and Qeynos, be a High Elf or gnome. Erudites are nice for the starting Int, but they can't see in the dark until level 16 when they get Summon Heatstone (I think). Plus gnomes and elves have racially modified charisma, dexterity and agility. I am a high elf mage and really like it, but if forced to pick another race, I'd go to the dark side because Neriak is such a cool city and the way the guild masters talk to you is really great.<br>Just my 2cp.<br>&nbsp;<br>Aaneldarie Tura'Seorsa<br>29th Season Magician  Vazaelle</td></tr>
